<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "1E">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "05">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "4">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A1504001" svcinfotypenbr = "06" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Oil Pressure Check
</title>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Prior to checking oil pressure, check the following points.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Oil level in oil pan
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If oil level is low, add oil up to full level mark (hole) (1) on oil level gauge. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1506004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<figure page = "2">
<graphic graphicname = "IYSQ01020012.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "45.200mm" ver = "01" gw = "160" gh = "111"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.968in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Low level mark (hole)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Oil quality
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If oil is discolored or deteriorated, change it. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1506004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Oil leaks
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If leak is found, repair leaky point.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<s1>
<ptxt>
For M/T model, place gear shift lever in “Neutral” and apply parking brake.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
For CVT model, place select lever in “P” and apply parking brake.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove front bumper. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9806001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove front bumper lower absorber. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9806002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Remove engine front cover (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B150001.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "71.620mm" ver = "01" gw = "174" gh = "187"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove exhaust manifold cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1B06001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
To avoid the danger of being burned, do not touch the exhaust system when the system is hot.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Any service on the exhaust system should be performed when the system is cool.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
With oil cooler outlet hoses connected, remove oil cooler water pipe (1) from cylinder block.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B150002.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "67.807mm" ver = "01" gw = "224" gh = "176"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect OCV connector.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect oil pressure switch lead wire (1).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove oil pressure switch (2) from cylinder block.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B150003.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "73.661mm" ver = "01" gw = "211" gh = "192"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install special tools to threaded hole where oil pressure switch was removed.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L1E001">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09915-77311">
09915–77311
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L1E002">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09915-78211">
09915–78211
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B150004.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "89.288mm" ver = "01" gw = "213" gh = "237"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Start engine and warm it up to normal operating temperature.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
After warming up, raise engine speed to 4,000 rpm and measure oil pressure.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Oil pressure specification
</title>
<ptxt>
More than 270 kPa (2.8 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 39.2 psi) at 4,000 rpm.
</ptxt>
</spec>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
After checking oil pressure, stop engine and remove special tools.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply sealant to thread portion of oil pressure switch (1), and then tighten oil pressure switch to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
If sealant is applied to the hole when applying sealant to thread portion of the oil pressure switch, the engine oil pressure light will not operate properly due to clogging.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Avoid applying sealant to the oil pressure switch hole.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<materials>
<materialitem name = "Thread Lock Cement Super 1322" id = "M1E001" uid = "37">
<m-part>
“A”
</m-part>
<m-desc>
Thread lock cement
</m-desc>
<m-number>
99000–32110
</m-number>
<m-name>
Thread Lock Cement Super 1322
</m-name>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</materialitem>
</materials>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T1E001">
<t-part>
Oil pressure switch
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
13
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
1.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
9.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B150005.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "66.706mm" ver = "01" gw = "209" gh = "173"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect oil pressure switch lead wire (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B150006.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "70.793mm" ver = "01" gw = "223" gh = "184"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect OCV connector.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Start engine and check oil pressure switch for oil leakage. If oil leakage is found, repair incorrect installation of oil pressure switch.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install oil cooler water pipe (1) to cylinder block.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B150002.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "67.807mm" ver = "01" gw = "224" gh = "176"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install exhaust manifold cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1B06001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install engine front cover (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B150001.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "71.620mm" ver = "01" gw = "174" gh = "187"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install front bumper lower absorber. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9806002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install front bumper. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9806001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1104003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If any DTC is displayed, clear DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1104004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
